p: The values of relative cell proliferation percentage of the aqueous extract (Fig.Â 5) showed a proliferative effect at concentrations of 0.25% and 0.50% v/v in the Trypan blue test, although the MTT test did not show a significant difference compared to the control. However, in both tests there was a tendency of the relative cell proliferation percentage to decrease, starting at a concentration of 2% v/v of the extract. The decrease in the values of the relative cell proliferation percentage in the trypan blue assay was higher than in the MTT test.
